worker node (data plane)

kubelet > it ensures the pod is always in running state
kubeproxy > for networking purpose
container runtime > responsible for running containers eg: docker,containerd

Master node (control plane)

API server > it expose your Kubernetes 
scheduler > responsible for scheduling resource in k8s
etcd > store entire cluster data in key-value format
controller manager > maintain the state of the pods like Replicaset
